caption: We ordered two pad thais, one with chicken and one with shrimp, and we asked for onions on both and to not ring the doorbell when delivering (we had sleeping babies). The chicken pad thai tasted very shrimpy, and then I found a shrimp tail in it. Thankfully I don’t have a shellfish allergy, but it appears they cooked one dish together with shrimp and then separated it into two bowls and tried to pick out the shrimp and add chicken to one. Additionally, neither had onions as requested. And the delivery man not only rang the doorbell but repeatedly knocked loudly. Will not be trying again.

So I ordered from this restaurant on a whim via Grubhub. The food was so yummy. I had the crab fried rice without onions. First they actually complied with my no onions request (this can be hot or miss). Second the food was delicious. Perfectly seasoned with the right ingredients to make it great. Tip: request two lines to be included in if you get the crab fried rice. The lime juice takes it to another level for me. Lol. Based on my experience yesterday I don’t think you’ll be disappointed. Give this place a try! You’re welcome foodie friends. 😊
